Casino, Excel, GFI Informatique: French Equity Market Preview

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-06-29T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/casino-excel-gfi-informatique-french-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual price changes in Paris. Symbols
are in parentheses after company names and prices are from the
last close.  France ’s  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  climbed 1.4 percent to 3,851.89.  Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA (CO)  : The supermarket
operator asked Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de
Acucar’s Chairman Abilio Diniz to immediately call a board
meeting to discuss the proposal to merge Pao de Acucar and
 Carrefour SA (CA) ’s unit in Brazil. Pao de Acucar disclosed the
request from Casino in a regulatory filing. The shares fell 5.6
percent to 62.20 euros.  Excel Industries SA (EXE FP): The maker of spray equipment
said third-quarter sales rose to 146.2 million euros from 119.4
million euros and it expects faster growth in the fourth
quarter. The shares rose 0.6 percent to 40.55 euros.  GFI Informatique (GFI)  : The computer services company
said it will issue 50 million euros of convertible bonds. The
stock gained 0.3 percent to 3.81 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
 markdeen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root in Paris at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net  